<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870115-0120 </DOCNO><HL> NCA to Post 4th-Period Loss</HL><DD> 01/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NCAC </IN><DATELINE> SANTA CLARA, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   NCA Corp. said it expects to report a fourth-quarter loss of as much as $1.3 million because of lower-than-anticipated software-license revenue and increased marketing expenditure.    The maker of computer-software systems said the loss it expects to report will include a $275,000 charge from a settlement with the Internal Revenue Service concerning NCA's 1980 federal tax return.    In the year-earlier quarter, NCA's net loss was $3.6 million on revenue of $4.6 million. </TEXT></DOC>